        <h1>5 Ingredient Chili</h1>

        <ul>

            <a href="recipes/5-ingredient-chili.jpeg">5 Ingredient Chili</a>

        </ul>

        <h2>Chili Recipe</h2>

        <p>This is a great chili recipe that is very easy and fast to make that everyone will enjoy!</p>

        <h2>Ingredients</h2>

        <ul>
            <li>1 pound lean ground beef</li>
            <li>1 (15 ounces) can tomato sauce</li>
            <li>1 (15ounce) can of kidney beans, drained</li>
            <li>1 (15 ounce) can of chili beans, not drained</li>
            <li>2 tbsp chili powder, or to taste</li>
            <li>1 cup shredded cheddar cheese</li>
            <li>salt and pepper to taste</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Directions</h2>

        <ol>
            <li>1. In a large skillet over medium heat brown the ground beef for about 5-7 minutes</li>
            <li>2. Add the kidney beans, chili beans and tomato sauce stirring until boiling</li>
            <li>3. Reduce heat to a simmer and add the chili powder to taste</li>
            <li>4. Allow chili to thicken on simmer to desired consistency</li>
            <li>5. Serve warm with shredded cheese on top if desired</li>
        </ol>

